UNITED STATES of America ex rel. John H. CLOUTHIER, Appellant, v. James F. MARONEY, Superintendent, State Correctional Institution, Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. No. 14847. United States Court of Appeals Third Circuit. Submitted Dec. 7, 1964. Decided Feb. 5, 1965. John J. Clouthier, pro se. James C. Crumlish, Jr., Philadelphia, Pa. (John F. Hassett, Asst. Dist. Atty., Thomas M. Reed, Chief Asst. Dist. Atty., Prosecution Dept., F. Emmett Fitzpatrick, Jr., First Asst. Dist. Atty., Philadelphia, Pa., on the brief), for ap-pellee.

Before GANEY, SMITH and FREEDMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment denying the application for writ of habeas corpus is affirmed on the opinion of the lower court by Judge Rosenberg, D.C., 238 F.Supp. 161.
